## Pull request checklist

Use [.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md](.github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md) when opening a PR. It captures tier, testing notes, context updates, and stack verification.

## Architecture decisions (Tier S)

Tier **S** changes (schema, security, infrastructure) need an analysis pass and an ADR **before** implementation. Copy `docs/decisions/000-template.md` to a new numbered file and record the decision there.

## Versioning

This project follows **semantic versioning**. The canonical version lives in the `VERSION` file at the repo root; bump it when you release, tag the commit (`vMAJOR.MINOR.PATCH`), and keep changelog or release notes in line with user-visible changes.

